results.name: Denominators of coefficients arising from q-expansion of Integrate[eta[q^4]^8/eta[q^2]^4, q]/q where eta is the Dedekind eta function.
comment: Gosper observes that A225699/A225700 = A008438/(2,4,6,8,10,...) and hence the coefficient of q^k in the q-expansion is 1 iff k is an odd prime (see Example section below).
Note that, as usual in the OEIS, the q-expansion has been normalized here to avoid having every other term be zero.
reference: R. W. Gosper, Posting to the Math Fun Mailing List, Jun 01 2013
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, Jun 01 2013
